to learn as software to any interested tribal members and is also taught at the tribal school. There is no information about how the language is currently used.%0a%3c  %0a%3c Second Pass of Information: %0a%3c %0a%3c The IPA transcription of the tribe name is /tʃɪtɪməʃɑː/. The language is referred to as ‘Chitimacha Tribe’s language’ in both indigenous and non-indigenous sources.%0a%3c %0a%3c Wikipedia paints the Chitimacha Tribe as much more bystanders in the revival of their language - more credit is given to the linguist who recorded the conversations and the American Philosophical Society Library.  %0a%3c %0a%3c The language is also described as ‘extinct’ rather than received in secondary sources.%0a%3c %0a%3c The indigenous run source gives a much more detailed account of how they were forced to sell off their land because of taxes from the US government, which secondary sources do not mention.%0a%3c %0a%3c Indigenous-run source: %0a%3c http://www.chitimacha.gov/history-culture%0a%3c %0a%3c Secondary sources: %0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chitimacha%0a%3c https://www.cajuncoast.com/about-us/history/history-chitimacha%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: :)%0a%3c (:Category: IndigenousLanguagesOfTheAmericas:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
